The article applauds Congress for reauthorizing the Carl D. Perkins Career and Technical Education Act (Perkins) with bipartisan support. It emphasizes the importance of adapting to the evolving economy, which is increasingly dependent on STEM disciplines and skilled labor. The White House, led by Ivanka Trump, played a significant role in ensuring the passage of this legislation, which aims to provide students and workers with the necessary training to succeed in the 21st century economy. The article highlights the benefits of enacting this law, including preparing students for the changing job market and helping employers find the skilled workers they need to remain competitive.